The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of decision trees and neural networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the subcategories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential applications of facial expression recognition in marketing and healthcare, which could indicate a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or multimedia (cs.MM).
